The **Profiles **tab allows to create and manage build profiles, that is, groups of templates that will be included in a build. In particular, it allows to:

- Create a new profile. 

- Validate a profile.

- Build a profile.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

For each profile, the following information is displayed:

**Information**

**Description**

**Code**

The code assigned to the profile by the system.

**Description**

A description of the profile.

**Documents**

The number of documents grouped in the profile.

**Created on**

The profile creation date.

**Built on**

The date of the last build performed with that profile.

## Creating a new profile
- Click **New profileâ€¦ **The **Profile settings **panel appears.

![](data:image/png;base64,) 

- In the **Code **text field, enter the name of the profile.

- (optional) In the **Description **text field, enter a brief description of the profile.

- Select the documents to group in profile.

- Click **Apply **to confirm.

## Setting the default profile
- Select the desired profile from the list.

- Click **Make default**.

### **Removing the default profile selection**
- Select the default profile.

- From the **More actions... **drop-down menu, select **Remove default selection**.

## Building a profile
- Select the profile that you wish to build.

- Click **Build now**. The system runs the build process for all documents grouped in the profile.

## Validating a profile
- Select the profile that you wish to validate.

- Click **Validate now**. The system verifies that the build process has been completed successfully.

## Deleting a profile
- Select the profile(s) that you wish to delete.

- From the **More actions... **drop-down menu, select **Delete profiles...**.

- In the confirmation window that appears, click **Delete **to confirm.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

## Merging profiles
- Select the profiles that you wish to merge.

- From the **More actions... **drop-down menu, select **Merge profiles. **In the **Profile settings **panel, the documents of the merged profiles are selected.

- In the **Profile settings **panel, edit the **Code **and **Description **of the new profile that will be created.

- Select the documents that you wish to group in the profile.

- Click **Apply **to confirm.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

## Comparing profiles
> Note

*The Compare profiles... command compares the composition of the selected build profiles, allowing to check which documents are included in each profile. The profile details are shown side to side, allowing to change the profile composition by selecting (or deselecting) the desired documents.*

- Select the profiles that you wish to compare.

- From the **More actions... **drop-down menu, select **Compare profiles...**.

- Select the documents that you wish to group in the profiles.

- Click **Apply **to confirm.

![](data:image/png;base64,) 

- (optional) If desired, click **Merge the profiles **to create a new profile containing all the documents that have been selected in the profiles.
